To me, one of the best uses for Gen AI that I've seen other instructors incorporate into their classes are exercises that demonstrate its limitations. For instance, use Gen AI to write code (Python, SQL, etc.) answering a prompt, then analyze that code and see what it got correct/incorrect, then dig deeper to determine why it got certain elements incorrect. Did it miss context that a human would have understood? Did we provide an ambiguous prompt? Has it learned "bad" solutions from previous interactions that are carrying forward? This type of activity encourages students to think critically about Gen AI in specific as well as emerging technology in general.
